timelineItems.desc: A pair of clubs looking to hang on to playoff positions in their respective conferences meet when Seattle Sounders FC entertain Toronto FC at at CenturyLink Field on Saturday evening.
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: Seattle Sounders vs Toronto FC | September 5, 2015

timelineItems.name: Prost Amerika
timelineItems.text: As good as Seattle's looked so far with players Micheal Bradley and Herculez Gomez all it takes is one errant pass. #SEAvTOR

timelineItems.name: Radio Cascadia
timelineItems.text: Huge win for Seattle in the playoff race. #SEAvTOR

timelineItems.name: Daniel Squizzato
timelineItems.text: Look, I always want #TFClive to win, but am I surprised that, missing 6 starters, they lost on the road in Seattle? No, no I'm not.

timelineItems.name: Kyle Mayer
timelineItems.text: No points, but positive signs nonetheless. Time for the stretch run now. #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: Dan Riccio
timelineItems.text: Couple of bad moments loses a point for TFC. Overall a solid performance, given the circumstances. #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: Gareth Wheeler
timelineItems.text: Hard luck there. Undermanned. Up against it. Put in a shift. Plenty to build off of there. Big test next Sunday at home v. Revs. #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: Rob Ditta
timelineItems.text: There was a point there for the taking. Tons of credit to the Reds after that one. They put in an excellent effort. Unlucky. #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: Kurtis Larson
timelineItems.text: If I'm a #Sounders fan, I'm worried. That was TFC without arguably eight starters. More than most expected from the Reds.

timelineItems.name: Adam Kristian Smith
timelineItems.text: Talkin bout Oba! #EBFG (@ CenturyLink Field for Toronto FC vs Seattle Sounders FC) https://t.co/Pci1XNSpbd http://t.co/LFOtxT4Ys4
